tweets.full_text: It's not an official milady position--the only official milady positions are what's stated in the remilia manifesto and the core commitment to freedoms--but I also think it's healthy and funny for there to be radicals wielding milady as a weapon to push the space towards those values; I would only step in if it begins to contradict those values, though as a political project I do think it's more relevant they focus the energy on aligning the ETH ecosystem rather than outsider liquidity. It's an old contention with milady, remilio was partly in response to that energy, to give a space for trader and shitcoiner types that were getting attacked by purists. Remilia is a bigger umbrella than just milady and also bigger than crypto as an industry. We're building the new internet and milady is one cultural pillar.

tweets.full_text: I don’t do PR. You’re mixing up positioning for short/mid term PA with a debate over long term execution towards aligned decentralized values. I do believe in the goal of a world computer; I tempered my opinion on the ICO fork and came around to ETH prior to their recognition of milady after speaking to developers closely involved and also after getting to understand the low levels of sincerity and short time horizons of the other teams building “alternatives”. I still maintain some caution if they truly will execute on the goals they’ve set out to, but I’m much more convinced on their sincerity in trying. This is not the same thing traders focused on their short/mid term price performance are worried about though, and it’s not any advocation on those bets. I’m also not a hardline maxi, I’ve argued all volume flooding into decentralized markets is good overall for the goals of the space; the positioning debate between chains is primarily about risks & time horizons which is informed by the idealism, defensibility & alignment debates that place ETH on top among its competitors—of which BTC is not one. BTC solves an entirely different goal than ETH, people contrasting the two are just thinking of them in terms of bags.
